  {
    "title": "Speaking Freely: Shin Yang",
    "link": "https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2026/03/speaking-freely-shin-yang",
    "pubDate": "2026-03-04T19:47:03.000Z",
    "content": "<html><head></head><body><div class=\"field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden\"><div class=\"field__items\"><div class=\"field__item even\"><p><strong>*This interview has been edited for length and clarity.</strong></p>\n<p><b>David Greene: Shin, please introduce yourself to the Speaking Freely community.</b></p>\n<p><span> </span><b>Shin Yang</b><span>: My name is Shin Yang. I am a queer writer with a legal background and experience in product management. I am the steward of Lezismore, an independent, self-hosted, open-source community for sexual minorities in Taiwan. For the past decade, I have focused on platform governance as infrastructure, with a particular emphasis on anonymity, minimal data collection, and behavior-based accountability, so that people can speak about intimacy </span></p></div></div></div></body></html>",
