  {
    "title": "EFF to Supreme Court: Shut Down Unconstitutional Geofence Searches",
    "link": "https://www.eff.org/press/releases/eff-supreme-court-shut-down-unconstitutional-geofence-searches",
    "pubDate": "2026-03-03T15:54:57.000Z",
    "content": "<html><head></head><body><div class=\"field field--name-field-pr-subhead field--type-text field--label-hidden\"><div class=\"field__items\"><div class=\"field__item even\">Digital Dragnets Violate Fourth Amendment, Brief Argues </div></div></div><div class=\"field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden\"><div class=\"field__items\"><div class=\"field__item even\"><p>WASHINGTON, D.C. – The Electronic Frontier Foundation (EFF), the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU), the ACLU of Virginia, and the Center on Privacy &amp; Technology at Georgetown Law filed a brief Monday urging the U.S. Supreme Court to rule that invasive geofence warrants are unconstitutional.</p>\n<p><span data-contrast=\"auto\">The brief argues that geofence warrants—which compel companies to provide information on every e</span></p></div></div></div></body></html>",
